                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12682254" author="charith" created="Mon, 16 Mar 2009 09:03:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There was a small bug in the code that causes the issue&lt;br/&gt;
this is the patch to resolve the bug&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then i got a another error &lt;br/&gt;
that occues when SynapseContoller try to build the ConfigurationContext&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m working on that error to resolve this issue&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12682293" author="charith" created="Mon, 16 Mar 2009 11:59:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch to resolve the complete issue&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;problems solved&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1.there was a bug in the code which try to set the synapse home in the place where server name should   &lt;br/&gt;
2.synapse war does not contain nessory jars that need to build the ConfigurationContext (eg: axis2 transports )&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;please review and commit &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12682568" author="charith" created="Tue, 17 Mar 2009 06:07:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi ,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;since synapse.war --&amp;gt; WEB-INF/lib does not contain some of the dependencies defined in the parent pom (which is needed  to start synapse ). I had to explicitly define them  in the war modules pom.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if there is a better way to do it please suggest.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;thank you,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Charith &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12688426" author="veithen" created="Mon, 23 Mar 2009 21:27:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in trunk. Thanks for spotting this issue!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;PS: For the dependency issue, there is indeed a better way. The pom.xml included the synapse-xxx JARs in an incorrect way (maybe related to some bug in older versions the maven-war-plugin). The right way is to declare them as dependencies. Maven will then take care of the rest (i.e. including the transitive dependencies).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
